{
  "texts": [
    "This hybrid approach emerged as a practical solution to the challenges posed by increasingly complex hardware architectures.",
    "It offers a viable pathway to deriving safe and reliable WCET estimates in contexts where traditional static analysis methods would require lengthy analysis times and often provide overestimated WCET.",
    "By integrating measurements with static analysis, hybrid methods can offer more accurate and efficient WCET estimates, accommodating the intricacies of modern hardware while reducing the conservatism inherent in purely static approaches.",
    "Deterministic AnalysisMBDTA is an adopted method for estimating the WCET in safety-critical systems.",
    "This approach relies on collecting execution time measurements from the actual hardware platform and analyzing these measurements to derive WCET estimates."
  ]
}